<h2>Groovy and Grails</h2>

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" class="bodytext" width="100%">
  <tr valign="top">
	<td class="formrequired">Summary:</td>
	<td>&nbsp;</td>
	<td>
      
	
	
	  <div style="float:right; width:145px; margin: 0 0 9px 15px;">
		
	    <div style="margin-bottom:4px;"><a title="Classroom Classes" alt="Classroom Classes" href="/portals/www/search/results.cfm?ui=www_edu&menu=search-results&searchtype=simple&category=schedule&id_subject=18353&deliveryType=1&filters=deliveryType"><img src="/ui/images/buttons/en/btnbluelarge_classroom-classes.png" width="145" height="21" alt="Classroom Classes" border="0" align="absmiddle" /></a></div>
		
	    <div style="margin-bottom:4px;"><a title="Live Online Classes" alt="Live Online Classes" href="/portals/www/search/results.cfm?ui=www_edu&menu=search-results&searchtype=simple&category=schedule&id_subject=18353&deliveryType=16&filters=deliveryType"><img src="/ui/images/buttons/en/btnbluelarge_live-online-classes.png" width="145" height="21" alt="Live Online Classes" border="0" align="absmiddle" /></a></div>
		
	    <div style="margin-bottom:4px;"><a title="Inquire about Onsite" alt="Inquire about Onsite" href="/mgrReg/message.cfm?ui=www_edu&subject=Onsite%20Training&id_subject=18353"><img src="/ui/images/buttons/en/btnbluelarge_inquire-about-onsite.png" width="145" height="21" alt="Inquire about Onsite" border="0" align="absmiddle" /></a></div>
		
	    <div style="margin-bottom:4px;"><a title="Course Datasheet" alt="Course Datasheet" href="/descriptions/EDU_DATASHEET_GroovyGrails_V11.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="/ui/images/buttons/en/btngraylarge_course-datasheet.png" width="145" height="21" alt="Course Datasheet" border="0" align="absmiddle" /></a></div>
		
	  </div>
	
      <div style="margin-top:1px;">
        - Formats:
		
        <strong style="color:#0C8D63;">Classroom</strong>, 
        <strong style="color:#0C8D63;">Live Online</strong>, 
        <strong style="color:#0C8D63;">Onsite</strong> 
      </div>
	
	  <div>- Length: 3 Days</div>
	
      <div style="padding-top:15px;">
		<div><strong>Overview:</strong></div>
	    <div><p align="justify">This 3-day intensive training covers both Groovy and Grails in great detail. After a thorough introduction to the technology, students are taken through many advanced aspects of both the<img src="http://www.springsource.org/files/groovy-grails-logo.png" align="right" hspace="10" alt="Grails"/> Groovy programming language and the Grails web application framework.<br><br>This training is designed to quickly move teams beyond the basics and on to the most powerful aspects of both Groovy and Grails. Students should expect intensive, hands-on interactive lab work.<br><br>The Groovy & Grails training by VMware is the only official Grails.org and Groovy.codehaus.org training in the world and is the perfect training if:<br><ul><li>You are interested in building web applications with Groovy & Grails<br><li>You are interested in learning a language that makes modern programming features available to Java developers with almost zero learning curve<br><li>You are working on/have planned an upcoming Groovy & Grails project<br><li>You are interested in working with a language that builds on the strengths of Java but has additional power features inspired by languages like Python, Ruby and Smalltalk<br><li>You like to increase developer productivity by reducing scaffolding code when developing web, GUI, database or console applications</ul></div>
	  </div>
		
	</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="3"><hr /></td>
  </tr>
	
		
	
  <tr valign="top">
	<td class="formrequired">Objectives:</td>
	<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
	<td class="bodytext">At the end of the training, you should gain an understanding of the Groovy programming language and the associated framework Grails, and you should be able to do the following:<br><ul><li>Write programs using Groovy<br><li>Integrate with Java<br><li>Use Grails for Web development and persistence<br><li>Have a sound knowledge of all the core concepts from the Web to the persistence layer<br><li>Understand key development best practices that enable the development of higher quality code</ul></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="3">&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
		
  <tr valign="top">
	<td class="formrequired" nowrap="nowrap">Intended Audience:</td>
	<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
	<td class="bodytext">This training is designed for:<br><br><li>Developers<br><li>Architects</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="3">&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
		
  <tr valign="top">
	<td class="formrequired">Prerequisites:</td>
	<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
	<td class="bodytext"><li>Experience with developing applications using Java</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="3">&nbsp;</td>
  </tr>
		
  <tr valign="top">
	<td class="formrequired">Outline:</td>
	<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
	<td class="bodytext">Day 1: The Groovy Language<br><ul><li>Introduction to Groovy <br><li>Installation and Tools<br><li>Groovy Beans<br><li>Language Fundamentals<br><li>Collections and Closures<br><li>Miscellaneous APIs, Java Interoperability, and Metaprogramming<br><li>Groovy Testing<br></ul>Day 2: Developing Enterprise Applications with Grails<br><ul><li>Introduction to Grails<br><li>Installation, Grails Quick Start<br><li>Scaffolding<br><li>GORM and Controllers<br></ul>Day 3: Services, Tag Libraries and Plug-Ins<br><ul><li>Services<br><li>Grails and Spring<br><li>GSP, Tag Libraries, and GSP Templates<br><li>Sitemesh Layout, Ajax<br><li>Grails Plug-ins<br></ul>Questions? Contact our <a target="_new" href="http://mylearn.vmware.com/contact.cfm?ui=www_edu">SpringSource/VMware Helpdesk</a><br><br><a href="http://mylearn.vmware.com/ilearn/MgrReg/faq.cfm?ui=www_edu&category=Customer%20Education">FAQ</a> | <a href="http://www.springsource.com/training/onsite">Onsite Training</a> | <a href="http://mylearn.vmware.com/ilearn/MgrReg/faq.cfm?ui=www&category=Customer%20Education">Terms & Conditions</a><br><br><img src="http://drh.img.digitalriver.com/DRHM/Storefront/Site/vmware/cm/images/nov09redesign/paymentmethods2.gif" align="middle" hspace="10" alt="SpringSource Payments"/></td>
  </tr>
